**Describe the bug**
I am aware that as of now polymorphic relations using model: * do not work, so i opted to use collection: *. But after i created one-to-many polymorphic relation, the dropdown in admin ui is disabled.

**Steps to reproduce the behavior**

1. Create two models (in my case post and menu-item)
2. Establish a one-to-many polymorphic relation as described in docs
3. Open admin panel
4. Create a couple of entries for each of those models
5. Go to either of those content types
6. See that relation dropdown is disabled

**Expected behavior**
Dropdown should be enabled and you should be able to select and save polymorphic relationships.

**Screenshots**
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/47951826/85923875-50990700-b897-11ea-8995-c85d8700e504.png)

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/47951826/85923897-71615c80-b897-11ea-91c7-499938331165.png)

**Code snippets**
menu-item.settings.json
```
{
    "kind": "collectionType",
    "collectionName": "menu_items",
    "info": {
        "name": "MenuItem"
    },
    "options": {
        "increments": true,
        "timestamps": true
    },
    "attributes": {
        "title": {
            "type": "string",
            "required": true
        },
        "element": {
            "type": "dynamiczone",
            "components": ["menu.post", "menu.tag"],
            "max": 1,
            "min": 1
        },
