In your code, you use `const deferred = Promise.defer();` to create a new Promise. According to https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Mozilla/JavaScript_code_modules/Promise.jsm/Deferred this method is obsolete.

You should use the ES6 way: https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Promise

```
new Promise(function(resolve, reject) {
  if (ok) {
    resolve();
  } else {
    reject();
  }
});
```

